ce:section.ce:para:
In this study, a single-cylinder, air-cooled diesel engine (DICOM model, Italy) was used for conducting the experiments. A dynamometer (MPA-40 model; Iran) was applied to measure engine performance parameters. A pollution meter was used to measure engine exhaust gases with technical specifications given in Table 4
                        . Finally, the performance parameters and exhaust emissions (power, torque, specific fuel consumption, CO, CO2, UHC and NOx) were measured at different engine speeds of 1800, 2100 and 2400 rpm at full load (Fig. 5
                        ). The engine was run for 10 min to ensure the removal of residual previous fuel blends in the fuel line. After that the data acquisition was started. This procedure was followed for all the blends. All experiments were performed in three repetition.
